<Color=Green>Undead familiars are generally only used by those mages with an unhealthy interest in Necromancy.  While they vary in abilities, generally speaking they make decent guards and bodyguards, but beyond this are not much use.  Also walking around with an undead familiar tends to make the common folk at least wary of you, and the local clergy to start preparing their Turn Undead ability.  Therefore most mages with undead familiars tend to be those who prefer to work in isolation or in the dark.

<Color=Yellow>Generally having your undead familiar summoned around clerics is a very bad idea unless you are of a significantly higher level that the clerics<Color=White>